    "instructions": "Find the minimum number of set bits (Hamming weight) in the binary representation of 2023 * n for any positive integer n. Note that 2023 is an odd number. For any odd number m, there exists a multiple of m that is a power of 2 minus 1 (i.e., 2^k - 1), or more generally, we are looking for the minimum number of 1s in the binary expansion of m*n. Since 2023 is not a power of 2, we check if there is a multiple that is a power of 2 (impossible for odd m > 1) or a sum of a few powers of 2. Specifically, check if there is an n such that 2023*n = 2^a + 2^b + ... with minimum terms.",
